# .gitignore — PPL Study Guide (static site published to GitHub Pages)
# This is a dependency-free static site, so most of this is preventative:
# it keeps secrets, OS junk, editor files, and local tooling out of the repo.
#
# NOTE: .nojekyll is intentionally NOT ignored — GitHub Pages needs it committed.

# ---- Secrets / environment / credentials (never commit) ----
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.pem
*.key
*.pfx
*.p12
*.crt
*.cer
secrets.*
*secret*
credentials*.json
service-account*.json
*.keystore
.netrc

# ---- OS-generated files ----
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ---- Editor / IDE ----
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~
.*.swp
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# ---- Node (only if you run `npx serve` or add tooling) ----
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm/

# ---- Python (the README's `python3 -m http.server` dev server) ----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/

# ---- Logs / temp / caches ----
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
.cache/
